column5: There's some hefty female walleye passing by on the live Wolf River fish cam this morning, so spring has definitely arrived there.  http://www.wolfrivercam.com/wrc20171a_002.htm  Others: http://www.wolfrivercam.com/
Frogs are out here. Tell take sign of the spawn.  Thanks for posting! I lost this site and couldn't remember the name!!!
I'm pretty sure I saw a walleye with a lamprey attached this morning. I don't think I've every seen that on a walleye before.
I've caught a few, but... I think two falls ago I caught about a 15" walleye with a half decomposed lamprey hanging about 6" out of its mouth! That was a first
